@node features "Features"

                               Features

-There's no complex installation: just run the game and play!

-A2Zee is a "Workbench" game, so it is meant to be played on the
 Workbench screen. The game window can be resized up to a maximum of
 640 x 160 pixels, and the game is redisplayed according to the new
 window size. If the window is too small, it will automatically be
 resized to an adequate displayable size.

-As the game uses as little of the computer's ressources as possible,
 you can run other applications, games, etc. at the same time.

-A2Zee works on all Amigas with Workbench 1.3 or higher.

@endnode

@node histo "History"

                               Versions History

  What follows are the various updates that were done since the first
version of the game.

1.0: -First public release.

1.01: -Unreleased test version.

1.02: -Bugfix: sometimes the game could crash when its window was
       resized.

1.03: -Some cosmetic changes were made (the game buttons buttons
       were altered, as well as some other improvements).
      -Other minor changes to the program code.

1.04: -New cosmetic changes (in the main menu, only the starting and
       ending letters are 'pressed down').
      -Other improvements to the game code.

1.05: -Some changes in the menu: if a player click on a lower letter
       than "H" it returns an "Invalid range".
      -Other minor changes in the program code.

1.06: -Bugfix: In game mode, when a player clicked on a tile containing
       a letter and then clicked anywhere else, that tile remained
       'pressed down'.
      -Some additional changes have been made to the program
       code:
        -The routine that generates the game window size has been revised.
        -various code enhancements.

@endnode

@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place A2Zee where you want on
your system (hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc.). No other files
or Libraries are needed.

                             How to play?

  When first run, A2Zee displays the main menu where a row of letters
from A to Z are displayed. The two letters that are 'pressed down', and
those that are between them, are the ones used for the game. By clicking
on one of the letters, you can choose how many letters you want to play
with, the minimum number of letters playable is 8 (A to H), but you can
play with all the letters (A to Z) if you want.

  When you are ready to play the game, just click on the 'Play!'
button. This will display the game board showing the letters you have
selected.

  When playing, click on a tile containing a letter you want to move and
click on the tile where you want to place that letter. At that moment,
the two letters will switch their positions.

  To complicate matters a little, each time you move some letters, the
letters located on either side of the letters to be moved will change
their position, as shown in the following example:

  A G C D E F B H
    ^         ^
    letters to be moved

The result:

  C B A D E H G F
    ^         ^
    moved letters

  Try to put all the letters in the correct order, in the least amount
of moves possible.

NOTE: you can go back anytime to the main menu by clicking on the
      windows close button.

  Have fun!

@endnode

